# Diagrams in Markdown (`.md`, `.mdc`)

## Prefer Mermaid over ASCII

- **Do not** use ASCII art, box-drawing characters, or monospace “sketches” for flowcharts, sequences, architectures, or state.
- **Do** use [Mermaid](https://mermaid.js.org/) fenced code blocks (` ```mermaid `) so diagrams render in viewers that support it and stay editable as text.

```markdown
<!-- ❌ Avoid: ASCII / box-drawing “plots” -->
┌──────┐     ┌──────┐
│  A   │────▶│  B   │
└──────┘     └──────┘

<!-- ✅ Prefer: Mermaid -->
```mermaid
flowchart LR
  A --> B
```
```

## Split busy diagrams

- If a single diagram has **many nodes**, **crossing edges**, or **unrelated concerns** in one canvas, **split it** into several smaller Mermaid blocks (e.g. one flow per subsection, or “overview” + “detail”).
- Each block should answer **one** question at a glance; link sections with short prose (“See … below”) instead of cramming everything into one graph.
